#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: pkgs.dbk:730
msgid "If the bug is related to the packaging, you just fix it.  If you are not able to fix it yourself, then tag the bug as <literal>help</literal>.  You can also ask for help on &email-debian-devel; or &email-debian-qa;.  If it's an upstream problem, you have to forward it to the upstream author.  Forwarding a bug is not enough, you have to check at each release if the bug has been fixed or not.  If it has, you just close it, otherwise you have to remind the author about it.  If you have the required skills you can prepare a patch that fixes the bug and send it to the author at the same time.  Make sure to send the patch to the BTS and to tag the bug as <literal>patch</literal>."
msgstr " url = \ " index.de.html \ " > tedesco < / ulink > e < ulink  url = \ " index.ja.html \ " > giapponese < / ulink > . "

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
