msgid "How could installing a package into <literal>testing</literal> possibly break other packages?"
msgstr "Se il traduttore non risponde , si può chiedere aiuto al corrispondente " mai" l10n . Se tutto fallisce , non dimenticate di mettere un avviso in  il documento tradotto , affermando che la traduzione è in qualche modo obsole che il lettore dovrebbe fare riferimento al documento originale , se possibi"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: pkgs.dbk:2815
msgid "The structure of the distribution archives is such that they can only contain one version of a package; a package is defined by its name.  So when the source package <literal>acmefoo</literal> is installed into <literal>testing</literal>, along with its binary packages <literal>acme-foo-bin</literal>, <literal>acme-bar-bin</literal>, <literal>libacme-foo1</literal> and <literal>libacme-foo-dev</literal>, the old version is removed."
msgstr " Evitare di rimuovere una traduzione del tutto , perché è obsoleto . Vecchio la documentazione è spesso migliore di alcuna documentazione a tutti per non"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: pkgs.dbk:2823
msgid "However, the old version may have provided a binary package with an old soname of a library, such as <literal>libacme-foo0</literal>.  Removing the old <literal>acmefoo</literal> will remove <literal>libacme-foo0</literal>, which will break any packages which depend on it."
msgstr " Come gestire un bug report riguardante una traduzione "

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: pkgs.dbk:2829
msgid "Evidently, this mainly affects packages which provide changing sets of binary packages in different versions (in turn, mainly libraries).  However, it will also affect packages upon which versioned dependencies have been declared of the ==, &lt;=, or &lt;&lt; varieties."
msgstr "La soluzione migliore potrebbe essere quella di marcare il bug come trasmesso  trasmette sia al traduttore precedente e la loro squadra ( utilizzando il mailing list debian- l10n - XXX corrispondente) . "

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: pkgs.dbk:2835
msgid "When the set of binary packages provided by a source package change in this way, all the packages that depended on the old binaries will have to be updated to depend on the new binaries instead.  Because installing such a source package into <literal>testing</literal> breaks all the packages that depended on it in <literal>testing</literal>, some care has to be taken now: all the depending packages must be updated and ready to be installed themselves so that they won't be broken, and, once everything is ready, manual intervention by the release manager or an assistant is normally required."
msgstr " I18N e L10N FAQ per i traduttori "

